Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 10:46:27 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] fix: split board page query + drop force-dynamic
 (server-query-perf)

BoardPage previously fetched the board with cards, sections,
submissions, members, quizzes, and all of their nested relations
in a single findFirst. For a freeform/grid/stream board this
returned several relations that the renderer never reads.

Changes:
- Round 1: board + getCurrentUser + getCurrentStudent run in
  Promise.all, collapsing three sequential awaits into one.
- Round 2: cards, sections, role, and layout-specific relations
  (submissions/members only for assignment boards, quizzes only
  for quiz boards) run concurrently.
- Drop `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` from seven
  auth-backed pages. They are still dynamic via cookies/auth(),
  but Next.js is now free to serve the Router Cache entry on
  back/forward navigation instead of re-running the RSC tree.

Affected pages:
- src/app/page.tsx
- src/app/board/[id]/page.tsx
- src/app/classroom/page.tsx
- src/app/classroom/[id]/page.tsx
- src/app/student/page.tsx
- src/app/quiz/[code]/page.tsx
- src/app/qr/[token]/page.tsx

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
